 and the group continues to function in residence at the University of Wisconsin. This book traces the Pro Arte Quartet's history from its beginnings to the present, highlighted byportraits of the diverse, fascinating, and colorful personalities, musicians and others, who have been a part of that history. The phases of its repertoires are analyzed, and the legacy of its recordings, many of pioneering significance, is reviewed. As a whole, the volume offers a panoramic window into a century of musical life. John W. Barker is Emeritus Professor of History at the University of Wisconsin-Madison. He is the author of Wagner and Venice (2008) and Wagner and Venice Fictionalized: Variations on a Theme (2012), both available from the University of Rochester Press.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMusical groups. 4aModern History. 4aMusic. 4aSocial History. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  abelgium.  acello.  acomposition.  aensemble.  ahistory of music.  amusic.  amusicians.  astrings.  atwentieth century.  auniversity of wisconsin.  aviola.  aviolin.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311143130740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781787441453?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787441453423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787441453/original  a978-3-11-143130-7  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles